4Geeks Academy offers a Cybersecurity Bootcamp that allows individuals to become cybersecurity specialists without any prior knowledge. The program provides a strong foundation in Windows, Linux, network, and server administration, as well as practical skills to secure these environments. Participants will also learn cloud security, penetration testing (both offensive and defensive), and cyber threat intelligence analysis. The bootcamp focuses on managing risks using data loss prevention strategies and complying with international standards like ISO 27001 and NIST. The program lasts for 16 weeks and includes three live online classes per week. The class size is limited to 16 people, and upon completion, participants will receive an official 4Geeks Completion Certificate that is recognized by multiple institutions. The median annual salary for cybersecurity professionals in the United States is $103,560. For more information, visit their website at https://4geeksacademy.com/us/coding-bootcamps/cybersecurity. Stop.